This is a standalone	Spark	Streaming	program	that	connects	to	Twitter	and does the following	
1) Prints	a	sample	of	the	tweets	it	receives	from	Twitter	every	second.	
2) Counts	the	number	of	characters,	words and	extract	the	hashtags	in	each tweet.
3) Calculates the	average	number	of characters and	words per	tweet
4) Counts	the	top	10	hashtags
5) Repeats the computations(3 and 4) for the	last	5 minutes	of tweets,	continuously every	30 seconds.
